      <h1>Bread Slicer Machine Price in India 2026</h1>
      <div class="article-meta">
        <span>📅 Updated: March 2026</span>
        <span>⏱️ 9 min read</span>
        <span>🇮🇳 India-focused pricing</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p><strong>Bread slicer machine prices in India in 2026 range from ₹25,000 for a basic manual/semi-automatic slicer to ₹3 lakh or more for a high-speed automatic commercial bread slicer.</strong> If your bakery sells pre-sliced bread, a good bread slicer is essential — it ensures uniform slices, protects bread from squashing, and dramatically speeds up packaging. This guide covers all types available in India with real prices and honest buying advice.</p>

    <h2>Types of Bread Slicers Available in India</h2>

    <h3>1. Manual Bread Slicer (Gravity Slicer)</h3>
    <p>A simple hand-operated machine where the bread is placed in a cradle and a row of parallel blades is pushed through the loaf. No electricity required. Produces clean, uniform slices but requires manual effort for each loaf.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Price:</strong> ₹8,000 – ₹25,000</li>
      <li><strong>Output:</strong> 4–8 loaves per minute (operator-dependent)</li>
      <li><strong>Slice thickness options:</strong> Typically fixed at 12mm or 19mm, or adjustable within a range</li>
      <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Small bakeries producing up to 50 loaves per day</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2. Semi-Automatic Bread Slicer</h3>
    <p>An electrically-powered slicer where the operator places the loaf and activates the cutting mechanism. Motor-driven blades ensure consistent, even cuts without manual pushing force. Much faster than manual slicers and produces more consistent results.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Price:</strong> ₹35,000 – ₹1,00,000</li>
      <li><strong>Output:</strong> 10–20 loaves per minute</li>
      <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Medium bakeries producing 50–200 loaves per day</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. Fully Automatic Bread Slicer</h3>
    <p>High-speed industrial slicers that feed, slice, and in some models bag the bread automatically. Used in industrial bakeries and large commercial operations. These are serious machines requiring dedicated space and electrical infrastructure.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Price:</strong> ₹1,50,000 – ₹5,00,000+</li>
      <li><strong>Output:</strong> 30–120+ loaves per minute</li>
      <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Industrial bakeries, large commercial operations producing 500+ loaves daily</li>
    </ul>

